               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My first wife and I parted by mutual consent; she proposed for me to sell her at Smithfield; I did not like to do that; there were writings drawn up between friends, and we separated; she consented for me to marry. I acted upon and that involved me into this unfortunate difficulty.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18110220-96-verdict521" type="verdictDescription">
